  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Preheat oven to 190C.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Onion:** halve, peel, and cut into medium dice. **Chili:** remove the seeds and thinly slice. **Garlic:** peel and coarsely chop. **Bell pepper:** remove the seeds, and cut into 1 cm squares.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Heat a large oven-safe skillet on medium heat, and add a generous amount of olive oil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the onion, chili, garlic, bell pepper, and salt. Cook until the onions are transparent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the onions are cooking, remove the cores of the large tomatoes, and coarsely chop them.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the chopped tomatoes and <Ingredient name=\"tomato paste\"  /> to the skillet, season with ground black pepper, cumin seeds, and smoked paprika. Add water, but not too much, not enough to cover the food. Bring it to simmer, and reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook for about 15 minutes, until the tomatoes soften and the liquid thickens.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Turn off the heat, and add more salt if necessary.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Using a spoon, push the vegetables to create a space for each egg. Crack the eggs into each space. Gently spoon a bit of tomato juice from the skillet over the whites, to help contain the eggs. Season each egg with a bit of salt and ground black pepper.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Carefully transfer the skillet to the oven, and bake for 6-10 minutes, until the egg whites are opaque and yolks have risen a bit but are still soft. The egg should move a bit when you gently shake the skillet.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Remove the skillet from the oven. Crumble some feta cheese over the shakshuka, and sprinkle with parsley or spring onions.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
